# 📄 JSONL Question Processor (Flask App)

This project is a simple **Flask web app** for processing `.jsonl` files that contain **QUESTION** and **SOLUTION** text. It automatically converts **options** `(1)(2)(3)(4)` or `(a)(b)(c)(d)` into `(A)(B)(C)(D)`.

---

## ✨ Features
- Upload `.jsonl` files from your browser  
- Process content directly in memory  
- Converts options inside **QUESTION** (always) and **SOLUTION** (only if options exist)  
- Keeps SOLUTION untouched if it doesn’t contain options  
- Preview the first 3 processed lines in the browser  
- Download the final processed `.jsonl` file  

---

## 📂 Example

**Input**
```json
{"body":{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"QUESTION (HTML one-line):\n<p>Which is correct?</p>\n(1) Option one\n(2) Option two\nSOLUTION (HTML one-line):\n<p>(a) Correct answer</p>"}]}}
Output

json
Copy code
{"body":{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"QUESTION (HTML one-line):\n<p>Which is correct?</p>\n(A) Option one\n(B) Option two\nSOLUTION (HTML one-line):\n<p>(A) Correct answer</p>"}]}}
